Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Halve, peel, and thinly
slice @Red Onion{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{} in a large pan{} over medium heat. Add onion
and cook, tossing occasionally, until nicely browned, ~{8-10%minutes}.

While onion cooks, halve and core @Bartlett Pear{1}. Thinly slice one half; cut
other half into ¼-inch cubes. Thinly slice @Fresh Mozzarella{4%ounce} or tear it
into small pieces.

Once onion is browned, stir half the @Balsamic Vinegar{5%teaspoon} and
@Sugar{1%tsp} into pan. Let reduce until syrupy, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove from pan and set aside in a small #bowl{}.

Place @Flatbreads{2} on a #baking sheet{}. Evenly scatter mozzarella over
flatbreads, then repeat with onion and sliced pear. Bake in oven until
mozzarella melts and flatbreads are golden brown, ~{10-12%minutes}.

While flatbreads bake, wipe out pan used for onion, then heat @Olive Oil{2%TBSP}
and a pinch of @Chili Flakes{1%teaspoon} (about ¼ tsp) in it over medium-high
heat. Immediately remove pan from heat once oil is hot and begins to bubble
slightly, ~{1-2%minutes}. Pour chili oil into a small bowl and let cool.

> For less heat, strain out the chili flakes using a fine-mesh strainer.

Place @Mixed Greens{2%ounce} lettuce, remaining cubed pear, a drizzle of
@Olive Oil{1%tsp}, and remaining @Balsamic Vinegar{1%tsp} in a large bowl and
toss to combine. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and more vinegar to taste.

Cut baked flatbreads into slices and drizzle to taste with chili oil. Serve with
salad on the side.